@@ -0,0 +1,100 @@
+# Hive install prompt (paste into Claude Code / Codex / Pi)
+
+A single published prompt the operator pastes into Claude Code, Codex, or Pi
+to install Hive end-to-end. It detects the OS, picks the brew / AUR / bash
+channel, runs the install, verifies `hive --version`, runs `hive init` in the
+current working directory, and — when the host agent advertises a real
+marketplace-add command — installs the hive skills package via that
+marketplace. The same text works across Claude / Codex / Pi because the
+channel commands are agent-agnostic shell.
+
+This prompt is **version-pinned**: it references a specific release tag's
+`install.sh` URL so re-pasting six months later installs the same version
+(the `latest` tag resolves to whatever was most recent at paste time; replace
+`latest` with a concrete `vX.Y.Z` for a hard pin).
+
+## Prompt (copy everything inside the ```text block)
+
+```text
+Install Hive on this machine and bootstrap it in the current working directory.
+
+Before changing anything, check stop-conditions and halt (report + ask) if any
+fail:
+- If `command -v hive` already succeeds AND `hive --version` prints
+  `0.1.0` or newer, skip the install section and go straight to `hive init`.
+- If `claude` is missing or `claude --version` is older than 2.1.118, stop and
+  report the missing prerequisite with the install hint
+  (https://claude.ai/code). Do NOT install claude yourself.
+- If `codex` is missing or `codex --version` is older than 0.125.0, warn that
+  the default execute agent will not work until Codex is installed, but
+  continue (codex is a soft dep).
+- If `gh auth status` fails, warn that PR/review flows need `gh` authenticated
+  but continue.
+- If the current working directory is not a git repository, stop and ask the
+  user which repo to bootstrap hive into.
+
+Detect the OS and channel:
+- macOS        → `brew install ivankuznetsov/hive/hive`   (Homebrew tap)
+- Arch Linux   → `yay -S hive-bin`                         (AUR)
+- Ubuntu/Debian/Fedora/WSL2/macOS-without-brew
+               → `curl -fsSL https://github.com/ivankuznetsov/hive/releases/latest/download/install.sh | bash`
+  (the one-liner verifies SHA256, installs to ~/.local/bin/hive, and falls
+  back to `hv` if a conflicting `hive` is already on PATH)
+- any other OS → stop and report that this OS is tier-3 / unsupported.
+
+Run the chosen channel command, then verify the install:
+  `hive --version`   (must print 0.1.0 or newer)
+  `hive doctor --deps`
+Report the version and the path returned by `command -v hive` (or `hv` if the
+one-liner fell back).
+
+Then bootstrap hive in the current working directory:
+  `hive init`
+`hive init` registers the daemon service (launchd/systemd) and PROMPTS whether
+to enable + start it now — answer per the user's preference (it never silently
+autostarts). If `hive init` exits 2, the project is already initialised; leave
+it and report that.
+
+Finally, install the hive skills package via the host agent's marketplace add
+command (skills are distributed separately from the core binary; see
+docs/skills-marketplace.md). If THIS agent supports a marketplace-add command,
+run it for the hive-skills marketplace URL. If you cannot determine the command
+or the agent has no marketplace, print the manual instructions from
+docs/skills-marketplace.md and STOP — do NOT copy-paste skill files into
+~/.claude/commands/, ~/.codex/, or ~/.pi/ by hand.
+
+When you are done, report: the channel used, the installed version, the binary
+path, whether the daemon was enabled, and whether skills were installed via the
+marketplace or left for manual install.
+```
+
+## Channel commands reference
+
+| OS / distro            | Channel command                                                                |
+| ---------------------- | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------ |
+| macOS (with Homebrew)  | `brew install ivankuznetsov/hive/hive`                                         |
+| Arch Linux             | `yay -S hive-bin`  (or `paru -S hive-bin`)                                     |
+| Ubuntu / Debian / WSL2 | `curl -fsSL https://github.com/ivankuznetsov/hive/releases/latest/download/install.sh \| bash` |
+| Fedora                 | (same curl\|bash one-liner)                                                    |
+| macOS without Homebrew | (same curl\|bash one-liner)                                                    |
+
+## Acceptance (install-plan scenario C)
+
+- Paste into Claude Code on macOS arm64 → installs via brew, `hive --version`
+  succeeds, `hive init` runs in cwd, the daemon autostart prompt appears,
+  skills installed via `claude` marketplace add.
+- Paste into Claude Code on Arch → `yay -S hive-bin`, same verification +
+  init + skills.
+- Paste into Claude Code on Ubuntu 22.04 → bash one-liner path, same.
+- The same prompt in Codex and Pi reaches the same end state (channel
+  commands are agent-agnostic shell).
+
+## Notes
+
+- The prompt explicitly halts before clobbering existing state, mirroring the
+  previous README block's stop-conditions.
+- Skills come only via the marketplace flow; a bare `hive init` (without this
+  prompt) leaves `~/.claude/`, `~/.codex/`, `~/.pi/` untouched.
+- Exact marketplace command names are an open question (install-plan FUQ #5);
+  until confirmed, the prompt prints the manual instructions and stops rather
+  than copy-paste files into agent dirs.
