+++ b/docs/skills-marketplace.md
@@ -0,0 +1,61 @@
+# Hive skills — agent marketplace distribution (U11)
+
+The **hive skills package** is a separate artifact, distributed through each
+agent's native marketplace flow. The core `hive` binary **never** installs
+skills; only the [install prompt](install-prompt.md) does, and only when a
+real marketplace-add mechanism exists for the host agent.
+
+This is a contract document, not a self-installing package. The actual
+`hive-skills` repo (marketplace manifest + skill bundles) lives in its own
+repository and is versioned independently of the core binary; it tracks
+Hive's CLI contract via the stable `--json` envelope + `schemas/`.
+
+## Non-goals (confirmed by the install plan)
+
+- The core `hive` binary does NOT write into `~/.claude/commands/`,
+  `~/.codex/...`, `~/.pi/...`. `hive init` leaves every agent's skill
+  directory untouched.
+- Skills are NOT copy-pasted by the install prompt when a marketplace is
+  unavailable — the prompt prints the manual command and stops.
+
+## Per-agent install
+
+Each supported agent exposes a marketplace-add command (exact names are an
+open question — install-plan FUQ #5). The intended shape:
+
+| Agent       | Marketplace add command (TBD)                  | Skills dir touched        |
+| ----------- | --------------------------------------------- | -------------------------- |
+| Claude Code | `claude marketplace add <hive-skills-url>`   | `~/.claude/plugins/...`    |
+| Pi          | (pi's package/skill add command)              | `~/.pi/agent/...`          |
+| Codex       | (codex's plugin add command)                  | `~/.codex/plugins/...`    |
+
+Until the exact command names are confirmed, the install prompt falls back to
+printing the manual command for the host agent and stopping — it never
+copy-pastes files.
+
+## Skill set
+
+The skills wrap the hive workflow verbs (`hive brainstorm`, `hive plan`,
+`hive develop`, `hive review`, `hive open-pr`, `hive finalize`, `hive archive`,
+`hive status`, `hive findings`, `hive approve`) as agent-callable skills, plus
+the `ce-brainstorm` / `ce-plan` / `ce-code-review` shapes Hive's templates
+already expect (see `lib/hive/config.rb` `DEFAULTS` per-stage `skill` fields
+and `templates/project_config.yml.erb`).
+
+## Stability boundary
+
+- The CLI contract (`--json` envelopes versioned via `Hive::Schemas`) is the
+  stability boundary the skills package programs against.
+- The skills package is versioned independently and may track a newer or older
+  Hive CLI than the locally-installed binary, as long as the `--json` envelope
+  version it consumes is supported.
+- Adding a new `error_kind` / `next_action.kind` / `tasks[].action` is
+  non-breaking by contract (callers MUST treat unknown values as no-ops);
+  renaming or removing one requires a `SCHEMA_VERSIONS` bump.
+
+## Removing skills
+
+Skills are removed via each agent's marketplace-remove command — NOT via
+`hive uninstall`. `hive uninstall` explicitly preserves every
+`~/.claude/`, `~/.codex/`, `~/.pi/` directory and prints a reminder pointing
+back here.
