+## [2026-07-11T09:50:00Z] install packaging — Hive as an installable package
+
+**Action:** Implemented the install plan (U1–U12): Hive is now installable as a packaged binary via a Homebrew tap, an AUR `hive-bin` package, a `curl|bash` one-liner, and a published paste-in install prompt. New subcommands `hive update` / `hive uninstall` detect the install channel and shell out to its native updater/uninstaller; `hive init` now registers the daemon service (launchd / systemd --user) with a TTY prompt to enable+start, and collects first-run global config (`defaults:` block) into `~/.config/hive/config.yml`. XDG paths replace the hardcoded `~/Dev/hive/` layout via the new `Hive::Paths` module, with legacy back-compat read + lazy migration on first write. `HIVE_HOME` remains honoured as a dev/test override so existing behaviour is byte-for-byte preserved. `hive doctor --deps` checks runtime CLIs (git/claude/bash hard, codex/gh soft; `jq` deliberately absent).
+
