+
+**TLDR**: Hive is installable as a packaged binary (Homebrew tap / AUR `hive-bin` / `curl|bash` one-liner / agent paste-in prompt), backed by tagged GitHub Releases of a self-contained vendored-Ruby (Tebako) binary. New subcommands `hive update` / `hive uninstall` detect the install channel and shell out to its native updater/uninstaller; `hive init` registers the daemon service (launchd / systemd --user) and collects first-run global config. XDG paths replace the hardcoded `~/Dev/hive/` layout, with legacy back-compat read + lazy migration.
+
+## Install-plan unit map
+
+| Unit | Artifact | Notes |
+|------|----------|-------|
+| U1 release + Tebako | `.github/workflows/release.yml`, `Rakefile` (`package:*`), `packaging/tebako/`, `packaging/checksums.sh` | Tebako FFI spike (bubbletea/lipgloss) MUST pass before wiring into the release workflow — install-plan Risk #1. |
+| U2 XDG paths | `lib/hive/paths.rb` (`Hive::Paths`), `lib/hive/config.rb` (`global_config_read_path`, legacy back-compat) | `HIVE_HOME` honoured as a dev/test override; XDG defaults when unset. Legacy `~/Dev/hive/config.yml` read transparently + lazily migrated on first write. |
+| U3 Homebrew | `packaging/brew/Formula/hive.rb`, `packaging/brew-sync.sh` | Binary formula, no `depends_on "ruby"`. |
+| U4 AUR | `packaging/aur/PKGBUILD` + `.SRCINFO`, `packaging/aur-sync.sh` | `hive-bin` always. |
+| U5 curl\|bash | `packaging/install.sh` | SHA256-verified; `hv` fallback on PATH conflict; writes `~/.local/share/hive/CHANNEL` marker. |
+| U6 hive update | `lib/hive/install_channel.rb`, `lib/hive/commands/update.rb` | Channel-native updater; never in-place swap. `--check` vs. GitHub Releases API. |
+| U7 hive uninstall | `lib/hive/commands/uninstall.rb`, `lib/hive/service.rb#uninstall_unit!` | Preserves `.hive-state/` + accumulated state even under `--purge`; never touches agent skill dirs. |
+| U8 service registration | `lib/hive/service.rb`, `templates/service/*.erb` | launchd plist (macOS) / systemd --user unit (Linux); TTY prompt to enable+start; non-TTY writes unit only. |
+| U9 first-run global config | `lib/hive/commands/init/prompts.rb` (`GlobalPrompts`), `lib/hive/config.rb#write_first_run_global_config!` | `defaults:` block in `~/.config/hive/config.yml`; skipped when config exists. |
+| U10 install prompt | `docs/install-prompt.md` | Version-pinned paste-in prompt for Claude/Codex/Pi. |
+| U11 skills marketplace | `docs/skills-marketplace.md` | Separate `hive-skills` repo via each agent's marketplace; core binary never writes skill dirs. |
+| U12 dep checking | `lib/hive/commands/doctor.rb` (`--deps`), `packaging/deps.txt` | Hard: git/claude/bash; soft: codex/gh. `jq` deliberately absent (FUQ #3). |
+
+## `Hive::Paths` resolution rules
+
+- `HIVE_HOME` set (dev / tests / pinned operator) → every Paths method returns the HIVE_HOME-rooted path (legacy behaviour byte-for-byte preserved; the daemon/bot tests set HIVE_HOME to a tmpdir).
+- `HIVE_HOME` unset → XDG: `~/.config/hive`, `~/.local/state/hive`, `~/.cache/hive`, `~/.local/share/hive`.
+- Shared assets (`templates/` `schemas/`) resolve via `Hive::Paths.resolve_asset` in order: `<bindir>/../share/hive/` (packaged) → `share_dir` (XDG) → legacy `~/Dev/hive/` → in-repo `lib/../` fallback (always works in dev/test).
+
+## Channel detection (`Hive::InstallChannel.detect`)
+
+1. `:bash` — marker file `~/.local/share/hive/CHANNEL` with content `bash` (written by `packaging/install.sh`).
+2. `:brew` — `brew list --versions hive` succeeds.
+3. `:aur` — `pacman -Q hive-bin` succeeds.
+4. `:unknown` — print help, exit non-zero.
+
+All subprocess probes are injectable (`shell:`) so unit tests don't need brew/pacman installed.
+
+## Test-only escape hatches
+
+- `HIVE_DISABLE_SERVICE_REGISTER=1` (set in `test/test_helper.rb`) — keeps the ~105 existing `Init.new().call` test sites from writing real plist/unit files to the operator's home. U8's own tests inject a fake `service_module`.
+- `with_tmp_global_config` (sets `HIVE_HOME`) — U9's `GlobalPrompts.first_run?` returns false under HIVE_HOME override, so existing init tests skip the first-run global prompt.
+
